WEBVTT

03:15.417 --> 03:17.593
What the fuck
are you doing?

03:17.720 --> 03:20.696
Fuck you!

03:24.568 --> 03:26.073
Oh, my God!

03:27.161 --> 03:30.937
Stop! Stop!

04:58.265 --> 04:59.801
<i>Good morning to you all.</i>

04:59.929 --> 05:01.241
<i>Good morning out there.</i>

05:01.368 --> 05:02.649
<i>Good morning to all of you.</i>

05:02.777 --> 05:04.473
<i>On this Monday...
Yeah, it's Monday.</i>

05:04.601 --> 05:06.200
<i>A case of the Mondays.</i>

05:10.393 --> 05:12.569
<i>I am on my third
cup of coffee.</i>

05:12.697 --> 05:15.321
<i>Anybody else having
a hard time this morning?</i>

05:18.073 --> 05:21.817
<i>Drivers are expected to
experience record congestion today.</i>

05:21.945 --> 05:25.113
<i>Around 100
workers are losing their jobs.</i>

05:25.241 --> 05:27.001
<i>Are you feeling
stressed out these days?</i>

05:27.129 --> 05:28.697
<i>Hey, guess what?
Join the club.</i>

05:28.825 --> 05:30.393
<i>Violent altercations
can happen</i>

05:30.521 --> 05:33.657
<i>from even the most
minor lapses by drivers.</i>

05:34.968 --> 05:38.169
<i>I've posted every day,
ten times a day, for three years now.</i>

05:38.904 --> 05:41.401
<i>Too many people out
there think they can multitask</i>

05:41.529 --> 05:42.969
<i>while operating a vehicle.</i>

05:45.785 --> 05:47.865
<i>Incivility
is a major issue in America.</i>

05:47.993 --> 05:49.753
<i>Rudeness can breed
more rudeness.</i>

05:49.881 --> 05:51.545
<i>We were born angry.</i>

05:51.673 --> 05:53.689
<i>And with anger
comes a lack of self-control.</i>

05:53.817 --> 05:56.633
<i>When you're very angry,
you lose a lot of self-control.</i>

05:58.393 --> 06:01.113
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

06:02.904 --> 06:04.633
- Oh, my...
- Oh, my God.

06:04.760 --> 06:06.233
Oh, my God!

06:08.153 --> 06:10.456
<i>Aggressive driving's been
on the rise for several years,</i>

06:10.584 --> 06:12.697
<i>and that's due
to societies moving faster...</i>

06:12.825 --> 06:15.737
<i>Road-rage
fatalities have skyrocketed 500%.</i>

06:17.657 --> 06:20.793
<i>A simple ride-share
trip yesterday took a horrific turn.</i>

06:20.921 --> 06:23.064
<i>Local law
enforcement is understaffed</i>

06:23.193 --> 06:24.665
<i>with no new applicants
in sight.</i>

06:24.793 --> 06:26.265
<i>It's getting
real bad out there.</i>

06:26.393 --> 06:27.832
<i>People are taking matters
into their own hands.</i>

06:27.961 --> 06:29.656
<i>Seeing this live right now.</i>

06:29.784 --> 06:31.833
<i>The police have him cornered.
We're in the middle of a standoff here.</i>

06:31.961 --> 06:33.817
I knew it wasn't
going to end well.

06:34.201 --> 06:35.897
<i>You gotta
protect yourself these days.</i>

06:36.025 --> 06:37.305
<i>No one else
is gonna help you.</i>

06:37.945 --> 06:40.505
<i>We've been married
15 years, we have three kids,</i>

06:40.633 --> 06:42.777
<i>and my husband's been
cheating on me for years.</i>

06:42.905 --> 06:44.792
<i>A man who is
thought to be the main suspect...</i>

06:44.921 --> 06:47.577
<i>Issues surrounding mental
health are increasing by the day.</i>

06:47.705 --> 06:50.233
<i>Inequality is pushing
us farther and farther apart.</i>

06:50.361 --> 06:52.217
<i>We are going backwards.</i>

06:52.345 --> 06:54.265
<i>Thousands of police
officers have been laid off since...</i>

06:54.392 --> 06:56.473
<i>It's a nationwide
epidemic right now.</i>

06:56.600 --> 06:59.480
<i>It could be years before
they can afford to hire more officers.</i>

06:59.609 --> 07:01.017
<i>...searching for a suspect...</i>

07:01.145 --> 07:03.065
<i>Gas prices
were up 82 cents today.</i>

07:03.193 --> 07:05.785
<i>Ambulance
response rates are slowing down.</i>

07:05.912 --> 07:07.961
<i>Stress levels
are at an all-time high.</i>

07:08.088 --> 07:10.905
<i>...all the warning
signs of impending collapse.</i>

07:11.033 --> 07:13.465
<i>When we reach our
boiling point and we explode...</i>

07:13.592 --> 07:15.641
<i>In the streets
with counter-protestors.</i>

07:15.768 --> 07:17.753
- <i>We blame the media, Twitter, Facebook.</i>
- <i>We feel all that strain...</i>

07:17.881 --> 07:19.673
<i>It's definitely
a problem that we're facing...</i>

07:19.801 --> 07:21.017
<i>Takes a toll
on your relationships.</i>

07:21.145 --> 07:22.809
<i>...your health
and well-being.</i>

07:22.937 --> 07:25.112
<i>Why is everything
filled with such garbage?</i>

07:25.241 --> 07:26.937
<i>People have
so much coming at them,</i>

07:27.065 --> 07:29.017
<i>their brains
just can't handle it.</i>

07:57.656 --> 07:58.585
Andy?

07:58.712 --> 08:00.345
<i>Hello. You up?</i>

08:00.825 --> 08:03.385
I am now.

08:03.512 --> 08:07.352
<i>Well, that's good, 'cause your
soon-to-be ex filed another motion.</i>

08:09.209 --> 08:10.745
What's he want now?

08:13.209 --> 08:14.585
Just say it.

08:14.713 --> 08:17.081
<i>He wants the house.</i>

08:17.497 --> 08:20.601
Of course he does.

08:20.729 --> 08:23.225
<i>Listen, I'm already
drawing up our objection.</i>

08:25.145 --> 08:27.929
Shit.
I didn't set my alarm.

08:28.345 --> 08:31.641
<i>Hey, I just need you
to tell me to file it, okay?</i>

08:32.633 --> 08:34.937
- <i>Rach?</i>
- I need to think about it.

08:35.065 --> 08:36.569
<i>What?</i>

08:36.697 --> 08:38.009
<i>Come on.</i>

08:38.617 --> 08:40.473
I just want this
to be over.

08:40.600 --> 08:42.776
<i>Rachel, you need to fight
this, and you know that.</i>

08:42.905 --> 08:44.889
<i>Come on. Richard didn't work
for the house. You did.</i>

08:47.161 --> 08:48.697
Hey, I gotta go.

08:48.826 --> 08:51.512
<i>Okay, but we're continuing
this conversation at lunch.</i>

08:51.641 --> 08:52.889
Yeah. You're the best.

08:53.017 --> 08:54.361
- <i>I know it.</i>
- Bye.

08:54.489 --> 08:56.153
Shouldn't you be dressed?

08:57.017 --> 09:00.281
What, this is not appropriate
attire for your personal chauffeur?

09:00.408 --> 09:03.353
- You have a client.
- No, I don't.

09:06.393 --> 09:08.665
I mean, yes, I do.
But, you know, we're still good.

09:08.792 --> 09:11.320
- It just means we've got...
- Another tardy.

09:11.449 --> 09:13.049
No, we're good.

09:14.200 --> 09:15.225
Okay?

09:15.353 --> 09:18.137
Yeah. No, I know.

09:18.265 --> 09:20.568
I... I get it.
I know you don't like living there,

09:20.697 --> 09:24.408
but it's an assisted-living community,
Mom, it's not an old folks' home.

09:26.041 --> 09:28.504
Can you hear me? Can you...

09:29.816 --> 09:31.545
Okay, Mom, you need...
I can't hear you.

09:31.673 --> 09:33.913
You need to press the little
microphone button. It's...

09:34.041 --> 09:36.057
<i>...firefighters battle
a raging house fire...</i>

09:36.184 --> 09:37.465
Mom, you need to...

09:38.360 --> 09:40.857
You need to press the little
microphone button with the...

09:40.984 --> 09:44.473
I don't know if you can hear me.
I'm gonna come see you later, okay?

09:44.601 --> 09:46.297
Um... Bye.

09:46.426 --> 09:49.049
<i>Police are actively searching now
for the homeowner's ex-husband,</i>

09:49.177 --> 09:52.409
<i>who was last seen fleeing the scene in
a gray pickup truck early this morning.</i>

09:52.537 --> 09:54.393
<i>Our own Pat Davereaux
spoke with a neighbor</i>

09:54.520 --> 09:57.560
<i>about the suspect's history
of substance abuse and violence</i>

09:57.689 --> 09:58.842
<i>after a workplace injury.</i>

09:58.968 --> 10:00.888
<i>She had
a restraining order on him.</i>

10:01.017 --> 10:02.233
<i>And now she's gone.</i>

10:02.360 --> 10:04.313
<i>He just couldn't face it.</i>

10:04.441 --> 10:07.097
- I was watching that.
- It's way too early for real life, dude.

10:07.225 --> 10:09.113
Anybody seen
my candy-cane scissors?

10:09.241 --> 10:12.249
Now, why would you
want to cut candy canes?

10:12.601 --> 10:14.777
You know.
My scissors with the...

10:17.050 --> 10:18.713
Never mind.

10:19.865 --> 10:21.177
Is she okay?

10:21.560 --> 10:22.681
I think so.

10:23.961 --> 10:25.561
Gonna be late again.

10:25.690 --> 10:26.873
Found 'em.

10:27.001 --> 10:28.953
Under one of your
piles of trash.

10:29.080 --> 10:31.801
Hey, science has proven

10:31.929 --> 10:34.681
that piles are the most
efficient filing system.

10:34.809 --> 10:36.441
I read that somewhere.

10:36.568 --> 10:38.136
Those are actually
my coupons.

10:38.713 --> 10:40.248
- Were you cutting us coupons?
- Mm-hmm.

10:40.377 --> 10:42.073
- I love you.
- Mm.

10:43.066 --> 10:46.937
Rachel, maybe you could learn a thing or
two from Mary about fiscal responsibility.

10:49.944 --> 10:52.249
- Rachel, I... I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

10:52.761 --> 10:55.577
I really love having you
and my brother here.

10:56.793 --> 10:59.000
But if you're so
fiscally responsible,

10:59.129 --> 11:01.016
maybe it's time to kick in
some rent here.

11:01.145 --> 11:04.217
Rachel, you're the one that said
that we couldn't stay at Mom's.

11:04.344 --> 11:06.680
We need to sell it.
And you know that. Okay?

11:07.193 --> 11:10.360
I can't afford to pay for her
care, and you really can't either.

11:10.489 --> 11:13.465
No, no, I told you,
I'm working on the business

11:13.592 --> 11:15.257
and it's gonna start soon.

11:15.385 --> 11:17.626
Come on, Freddy,
we gotta be real.

11:17.753 --> 11:19.064
Real about what?

11:19.673 --> 11:21.593
What does that even mean?

11:21.721 --> 11:23.864
She was getting lost
in her own neighborhood.

11:23.993 --> 11:26.713
But to be fair,
I still get lost in our old neighborhood.

11:27.193 --> 11:29.050
- Even with a phone?
- Yeah.

11:29.177 --> 11:32.217
Yeah, the streets in Linwood Springs
are like a freakin' maze of spaghetti.

11:32.344 --> 11:35.161
Kyle, grab a granola bar.
We gotta go.

11:35.576 --> 11:36.632
I already ate.

11:36.762 --> 11:38.841
Bye, guys.
See you after school.

11:38.968 --> 11:41.209
See you, dude.
Blow it up in there.

11:42.457 --> 11:43.672
Bye, buddy.

11:45.592 --> 11:47.129
Morning, Rachel.
Hey, Kyle.

11:47.257 --> 11:49.945
Morning, Rosie. New ride?

11:50.072 --> 11:51.066
Yeah. We've gone minivan.

11:51.193 --> 11:52.697
It suits you.

11:56.440 --> 11:57.433
Bye.

12:06.969 --> 12:08.506
Are we ever
gonna get a new ride?

12:08.632 --> 12:09.944
Sure.

12:11.512 --> 12:13.080
You wanna buy me one?

12:18.776 --> 12:20.121
"Prospective."

12:20.248 --> 12:21.786
Mom, I'm good.

12:22.233 --> 12:24.888
Remember,
it's not "per-spective."

12:25.369 --> 12:26.073
"Prospective."

12:26.200 --> 12:31.482
P-R-O-S-P-E-C-T-I-V-E.

12:31.608 --> 12:33.561
- "Prospective."
- Nice job.

12:39.993 --> 12:43.033
Hey, so what do you say?
Should we risk the freeway today?

12:43.192 --> 12:44.890
No. No freeway.

12:46.008 --> 12:49.177
Okay, well, just check
the traffic for me, please.

12:52.345 --> 12:53.977
You don't have
a pass code anymore?

12:54.104 --> 12:56.377
Not since I almost crashed
trying to unlock it.

12:56.506 --> 12:58.617
Wow. That's not safe.

13:01.050 --> 13:02.970
- "Precarious."
- What?

13:03.384 --> 13:05.464
Next word. "Precarious."

13:06.713 --> 13:11.641
"Precarious."
P-R-E-C-A-R-I-O-U-S.

13:11.770 --> 13:13.433
- Use it in a sentence.
- Uh...

13:13.944 --> 13:19.033
The way the glass is placed on the
edge of the table is precarious.

13:19.160 --> 13:21.210
Nice. Good job.

13:22.393 --> 13:23.737
Says it's clear.

13:23.864 --> 13:26.073
And that's a problem why?

13:26.202 --> 13:28.344
Because we still
can't trust it.

13:30.841 --> 13:33.946
- Sorry, kiddo, but today we must.
- Mom, no!

13:34.072 --> 13:35.961
- I don't have a choice.
- No! Please?

13:36.088 --> 13:37.881
- We're gonna be late.
- Trust me, Kyle.

13:38.008 --> 13:39.353
This is gonna be
quicker, okay?

13:39.481 --> 13:42.361
That's what you said
the last two times.

13:46.777 --> 13:48.697
Hey, see? All clear.

13:53.337 --> 13:55.577
It's Dad.
Can I please talk to him?

13:58.489 --> 14:00.409
- Hey, Dad.
- <i>Hey, man.</i>

14:00.537 --> 14:03.033
Uncle Freddy and I invented
a new Fortnite strategy.

14:03.160 --> 14:05.080
- You wanna hear it?
- <i>Not a good time.</i>

14:05.209 --> 14:06.841
- <i>Maybe later, okay?</i>
- Okay.

14:06.968 --> 14:08.697
You got the tickets
for the game tomorrow?

14:08.824 --> 14:10.456
<i>Yeah, look,
about the game...</i>

14:10.584 --> 14:12.376
<i>My schedule
kind of got messed up,</i>

14:12.504 --> 14:14.584
<i>and my boss needs me
to go out of town tomorrow.</i>

14:14.713 --> 14:16.953
- <i>Next time, okay?</i>
- Yeah, okay.

14:20.440 --> 14:22.297
That's really understanding
of you, Kyle.

14:22.424 --> 14:25.017
You know, new jobs,
like your Dad's, can be...

14:25.881 --> 14:27.961
really unpredictable
at first.

14:28.088 --> 14:29.530
<i>See. That's right.</i>

14:29.656 --> 14:32.281
<i>But I promise we'll make a
plan to go to a game soon...</i>

14:32.410 --> 14:34.744
Well, it probably shouldn't be planned.
It should be more a...

14:34.873 --> 14:36.889
a spur-of-the-moment
thing, right?

14:37.497 --> 14:42.232
I mean, 'cause plans...
can be hard to stick to.

14:42.361 --> 14:43.993
<i>Yeah. Yeah, yeah.</i>

14:44.121 --> 14:47.097
<i>I just need to keep my new boss
happy so I can get my own place...</i>

14:47.224 --> 14:49.434
Yeah, and maybe stop relying
on other sources of income.

14:49.561 --> 14:52.377
<i>Look, I just want
everything to be fair and square, okay?</i>

14:52.506 --> 14:55.513
<i>That's why I called, actually.
I needed to talk to you about moving...</i>

14:55.641 --> 14:57.784
Richard,
we gotta go, okay?

14:58.297 --> 15:00.281
We're just
getting to school.

15:00.408 --> 15:03.001
<i>Okay, fine. But, you
know, this isn't gonna solve itself.</i>

15:03.130 --> 15:05.528
<i>Look, I'm sorry again, bud.
I'll talk to you soon, okay?</i>

15:05.657 --> 15:08.281
- Okay.
- <i>Okay. All right. Bye.</i>

15:08.408 --> 15:10.072
Bye.

15:10.681 --> 15:11.928
Bye.

15:16.506 --> 15:19.129
I am... I'm sorry, Kyle.

15:28.794 --> 15:31.417
Three tardies
is an automatic detention.

15:33.048 --> 15:35.128
I'm doing the best
I can here. Okay?

15:38.457 --> 15:41.144
Seriously?

15:48.697 --> 15:50.457
I can't believe this.

15:56.026 --> 15:57.625
Deborah's calling you.

16:06.137 --> 16:08.888
Deborah. Hey, I was
just gonna call you.

16:09.018 --> 16:12.057
<i>I just wanted to make
sure I was gonna see you at 9:00.</i>

16:12.185 --> 16:15.161
- Absolutely.
- <i>Oh, great. I have a big day today.</i>

16:15.288 --> 16:17.624
Uh... but I've just hit
hellish traffic,

16:17.754 --> 16:21.657
so I'm gonna be 15,
maybe 20 minutes late, tops.

16:21.785 --> 16:23.288
<i>Are you serious?</i>

16:24.378 --> 16:26.137
Actually, you know what?

16:26.617 --> 16:29.144
It looks like
it might be clearing, so...

16:29.721 --> 16:30.904
We're good.

16:31.033 --> 16:32.984
<i>I can't
do this again, Rachel.</i>

16:33.114 --> 16:36.217
<i>You know what? I'm gonna call
Linda's guy and get in there.</i>

16:36.346 --> 16:39.256
<i>I love you, Rachel,
but ever since you lost your salon...</i>

16:39.384 --> 16:42.424
<i>I can't believe I'm gonna say this,
but you're fired. Get your shit together.</i>

16:42.553 --> 16:45.594
Deborah, no, wait. I'm sorry, okay?

16:48.761 --> 16:50.361
Oh, my God.

16:51.481 --> 16:52.952
Are you okay, Mom?

16:54.138 --> 16:55.225
Yeah.

16:56.250 --> 16:57.561
Just...

16:58.105 --> 17:00.090
Oh, my God. Just my...

17:01.177 --> 17:02.874
My best client,
that's all.

17:03.993 --> 17:05.368
I'm sorry.

17:10.104 --> 17:13.048
Eight miles, you know.
That's it.

17:14.137 --> 17:18.904
What takes ten minutes on a Sunday,
takes an hour every other day...

17:19.353 --> 17:20.985
and wrecks your career.

17:21.528 --> 17:22.969
You know why?

17:26.841 --> 17:27.705
Too many cars.

17:27.834 --> 17:31.578
Too many cars
and too many people.

17:32.056 --> 17:34.328
Didn't you also oversleep?

17:38.394 --> 17:40.314
Yes. Yes.

17:41.274 --> 17:44.121
And I overslept.
You're absolutely right.

17:47.257 --> 17:48.568
It's okay.

17:52.344 --> 17:53.689
So...

17:55.066 --> 17:56.538
any suggestions?

17:56.665 --> 17:59.418
You could take the next exit
and do surface streets.

18:02.968 --> 18:04.057
You got it.

18:04.185 --> 18:06.680
Hold on. I'm gonna
get us out of this.

18:10.393 --> 18:12.761
From now on,
no more freeways, okay?

18:12.889 --> 18:16.921
I only trust you,
okay? Deal?

18:17.593 --> 18:18.618
Deal.

19:08.601 --> 19:11.321
It's not getting
any greener.

19:11.801 --> 19:12.761
Come on, man.

19:12.888 --> 19:14.169
Come on!

19:17.433 --> 19:18.521
Go!

19:38.105 --> 19:40.856
No, no. Go.

19:41.530 --> 19:43.704
Oh, come on.

19:44.281 --> 19:46.009
Of course. Yeah.

20:06.937 --> 20:08.473
- Kyle, don't.
- Morning.

20:09.081 --> 20:11.480
I don't even get
a courtesy tap first?

20:12.249 --> 20:13.785
Roll up your window.

20:18.360 --> 20:19.641
It's not working.

20:19.769 --> 20:22.585
You know what
a courtesy tap is, young man?

20:22.713 --> 20:24.345
Just ignore him.

20:26.425 --> 20:28.473
Sounds like this.

20:28.601 --> 20:30.680
It's light. It's friendly.

20:30.808 --> 20:33.049
Just like you're trying
to get somebody's attention.

20:33.592 --> 20:35.353
I'm sure that's what
your mom meant.

20:35.801 --> 20:37.528
Is that right, ma'am?

20:37.657 --> 20:40.473
- Is a courtesy tap what you meant?
- No, it's not.

20:42.232 --> 20:43.481
Why is that?

20:43.609 --> 20:46.168
The light was green,
and you weren't moving.

20:46.297 --> 20:48.984
Mom. Stop it, please.

20:49.113 --> 20:51.289
Some of us
have places to be.

20:53.241 --> 20:56.121
Yeah, I admit to being
a little zoned out back there.

20:58.297 --> 21:00.601
I've been kind of having
a hard time lately.

21:00.729 --> 21:02.585
Yeah, well, join the club.

21:02.937 --> 21:04.376
Stop it.

21:04.505 --> 21:05.913
Well, I'm sorry.

21:07.609 --> 21:10.201
I'm sorry that you are,
and I'm sorry that...

21:10.329 --> 21:12.153
I might've made it worse.

21:14.041 --> 21:16.057
You accept my apology?

21:16.921 --> 21:18.648
Sure, whatever.

21:19.097 --> 21:20.185
Perfect.

21:21.081 --> 21:23.833
If you could just do the same,
we could press reset.

21:24.569 --> 21:26.713
Ma'am, I was saying,
if you could just apologize...

21:26.841 --> 21:28.280
Yeah, I heard you.

21:29.208 --> 21:30.425
And?

21:30.553 --> 21:33.080
I don't have anything
to apologize for, sir.

21:33.209 --> 21:35.577
- Mom. Just apologize.
- It's okay.

