1:02:57.241 --> 1:03:00.537
Dispatch, request assist...

1:03:08.697 --> 1:03:10.521
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

1:03:16.281 --> 1:03:17.370
Can you see him?

1:03:17.497 --> 1:03:19.161
He... He's catching up.

1:03:21.306 --> 1:03:22.904
Go! Go!

1:03:23.034 --> 1:03:25.528
Kyle, call 911 on the tablet.

1:03:27.673 --> 1:03:29.304
<i>911.
What's your emergency?</i>

1:03:29.432 --> 1:03:32.344
The man on the news,
he's chasing me in a silver minivan.

1:03:32.473 --> 1:03:34.328
- <i>Your current location?</i>
- Driving on 95 south.

1:03:34.457 --> 1:03:35.833
Just after the State exit.

1:03:35.961 --> 1:03:37.626
<i>Ma'am, all units
in that vicinity</i>

1:03:37.753 --> 1:03:39.706
<i>are currently responding
to a multi-vehicle crash.</i>

1:03:39.832 --> 1:03:43.064
He caused that accident!
My son and I are in danger!

1:03:43.194 --> 1:03:44.697
<i>Ma'am, we cannot
get to you at the moment.</i>

1:03:44.824 --> 1:03:47.130
<i>Stay on the line,
get someplace safe...</i>

1:03:47.768 --> 1:03:49.050
Mom, it died!

1:03:49.177 --> 1:03:50.905
Shit. Shit, shit, shit.

1:03:51.737 --> 1:03:53.689
Tell me
you have the charger.

1:03:54.681 --> 1:03:55.609
I don't.

1:03:55.737 --> 1:03:56.857
Oh, my God.

1:03:56.986 --> 1:03:58.328
We're on our own.

1:03:58.777 --> 1:03:59.961
Okay. Okay.

1:04:00.088 --> 1:04:01.848
We should just
go to the station.

1:04:01.976 --> 1:04:05.048
There's no way we can outrun him.
We have to lose him.

1:04:05.177 --> 1:04:06.968
- We need to go to Grandma's.
- Why?

1:04:07.097 --> 1:04:08.473
It's your strategy,
remember?

1:04:08.601 --> 1:04:09.817
- From the video game?
- What?

1:04:09.944 --> 1:04:11.864
It's somewhere
we're familiar with, okay?

1:04:11.994 --> 1:04:14.266
It's the safest place
to hide you.

1:04:15.001 --> 1:04:17.368
And we can call for help
with the silent alarm.

1:04:17.497 --> 1:04:20.121
And it'll confuse the heck out of
someone who's never been there before.

1:04:20.248 --> 1:04:22.489
Right, like Uncle Freddy
was saying.

1:04:22.617 --> 1:04:25.304
He still gets lost there,
like a maze of spaghetti.

1:04:25.434 --> 1:04:26.585
Yeah, exactly.

1:04:26.713 --> 1:04:27.768
So you think he'll get lost?

1:04:27.896 --> 1:04:29.337
For long enough.

1:04:43.770 --> 1:04:44.697
Drive!

1:04:44.825 --> 1:04:46.521
Go faster! Speed up!

1:05:44.377 --> 1:05:45.848
He's right behind us.

1:05:46.744 --> 1:05:48.153
He's catching up.

1:05:57.976 --> 1:05:59.288
Can you go any faster?

1:06:34.105 --> 1:06:35.353
Hold on!

1:06:43.769 --> 1:06:44.697
Fuck!

1:06:56.953 --> 1:06:59.576
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

1:07:13.657 --> 1:07:15.353
- Can you see him?
- No.

1:07:15.481 --> 1:07:17.656
I think he's still back
towards the entrance.

1:08:11.898 --> 1:08:12.921
Kyle.

1:08:14.265 --> 1:08:16.089
Starting now,
we stick to our plan.

1:08:16.216 --> 1:08:17.433
Our backup plan.

1:08:17.561 --> 1:08:20.377
Yeah, if we do that,
I promise you...

1:08:21.016 --> 1:08:24.153
we're gonna get through this
together, okay, you and me.

1:08:24.441 --> 1:08:25.561
- Yeah.
- Okay?

1:08:29.465 --> 1:08:31.065
Go. Go.

1:11:23.577 --> 1:11:26.041
Look at me! Look at me!

1:11:26.169 --> 1:11:28.248
Look at me. You see me?

1:11:28.729 --> 1:11:30.329
You're always gonna see me.

1:11:30.457 --> 1:11:33.144
I'm always gonna be
inside your head.

1:11:33.433 --> 1:11:35.609
Every time you think
of your little boy...

1:11:35.737 --> 1:11:39.768
and what you could've done
to save him.

1:12:17.049 --> 1:12:18.489
Kyle?

1:12:19.736 --> 1:12:21.144
Kyle Flynn?

1:12:22.841 --> 1:12:24.601
It's the police.

1:12:25.337 --> 1:12:27.097
You're safe, son.
Come on out.

1:12:30.329 --> 1:12:31.673
Come on, son.

1:12:41.304 --> 1:12:44.569
Your mom's hurt,
but she's okay.

1:12:46.809 --> 1:12:48.569
She asked us
to come and get you.

1:13:08.313 --> 1:13:09.721
Come on, son.

1:13:10.681 --> 1:13:11.993
It's okay.

1:13:16.441 --> 1:13:17.849
Come on out, boy.

1:13:47.865 --> 1:13:50.009
- I made a lot of noise.
- It's okay.

1:13:51.288 --> 1:13:53.689
No! No! No!

1:14:10.777 --> 1:14:12.985
No! No!

1:14:13.497 --> 1:14:16.313
Get off me! Let go!

1:14:22.649 --> 1:14:24.632
Mom!

1:14:24.762 --> 1:14:26.873
No!

1:14:28.280 --> 1:14:29.305
Mom!

1:14:49.369 --> 1:14:51.289
No! No! Mom!

1:15:08.088 --> 1:15:09.400
Hey!

1:15:21.080 --> 1:15:23.737
Here's your fucking
courtesy tap!

1:15:32.184 --> 1:15:33.656
You're okay.
You're okay.

1:15:35.672 --> 1:15:36.921
Mom.

1:15:51.513 --> 1:15:55.866
We understand that it may have
started as a result of a two-car crash...

1:16:17.753 --> 1:16:18.873
Ms. Flynn?

1:16:19.736 --> 1:16:21.529
May I have a moment?

1:16:22.553 --> 1:16:24.569
It's okay.
We'll be right back.

1:16:25.209 --> 1:16:26.264
Okay?

1:16:28.120 --> 1:16:32.216
I'm so sorry...

1:16:45.337 --> 1:16:46.968
Uncle Fred's alive.

1:16:48.248 --> 1:16:49.337
He is?

1:16:49.977 --> 1:16:51.385
He's gonna be okay.

1:16:51.513 --> 1:16:52.409
Can we go see him?

1:16:52.537 --> 1:16:54.617
Yeah. Yeah.

1:16:54.744 --> 1:16:57.528
We got your statement,
so you are free to go.

1:17:41.144 --> 1:17:42.426
What's your problem?

1:17:51.897 --> 1:17:53.497
Good choice.
